
[1]stiffly

   STIFFLY, adv.

   1. Firmly; strongly; as the boughs of a tree stiffly upheld.

   2. Rigidly; obstinately; with stubbornness. The doctrine of the
   infallibility of the church of Rome is stiffly maintained by its
   adherents.
